Class.Name: NSCell
Class.Description: A mechanism for displaying text or images in a view object without the overhead of a full NSView subclass.

InstanceMethods.Name: initImageCell:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSCell object initialized with the specified image and set to have the cell’s default menu.

InstanceMethods.Name: initTextCell:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an NSCell object initialized with the specified string and set to have the cell’s default menu.

InstanceMethods.Name: setCellAttribute:to:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the value for the specified cell attribute.

InstanceMethods.Name: cellAttribute:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the value for the specified cell attribute.

InstanceMethods.Name: setNextState
InstanceMethods.Description: Changes cell’s state to the next value in the sequence.

InstanceMethods.Name: setUpFieldEditorAttributes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Configures the textual and background attributes of the receiver's field editor.

InstanceMethods.Name: sendActionOn:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the conditions on which the receiver sends action messages to its target.

InstanceMethods.Name: menuForEvent:inRect:ofView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the menu associated with the cell and related to the specified event and frame.

InstanceMethods.Name: compare:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares the string values of the receiver another cell, disregarding case.

InstanceMethods.Name: performClick:
InstanceMethods.Description: Simulates a single mouse click on the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: takeObjectValueFrom:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the value of the receiver’s cell to the object value obtained from the specified object.

InstanceMethods.Name: takeIntegerValueFrom:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the value of the receiver’s cell to an integer value obtained from the specified object.

InstanceMethods.Name: takeIntValueFrom:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the value of the receiver’s cell to an integer value obtained from the specified object.

InstanceMethods.Name: takeStringValueFrom:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the value of the receiver’s cell to the string value obtained from the specified object.

InstanceMethods.Name: takeDoubleValueFrom:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the value of the receiver’s cell to a double-precision floating-point value obtained from the specified object.

InstanceMethods.Name: takeFloatValueFrom:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the value of the receiver’s cell to a single-precision floating-point value obtained from the specified object.

InstanceMethods.Name: trackMouse:inRect:ofView:untilMouseUp:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initiates the mouse tracking behavior in a cell.

InstanceMethods.Name: startTrackingAt:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Begins tracking mouse events within the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: continueTracking:at:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether mouse tracking should continue in the receiving cell.

InstanceMethods.Name: stopTracking:at:inView:mouseIsUp:
InstanceMethods.Description: Stops tracking mouse events within the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: getPeriodicDelay:interval:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the initial delay and repeat values for continuous sending of action messages to target objects.

InstanceMethods.Name: hitTestForEvent:inRect:ofView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns hit testing information for the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: resetCursorRect:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the receiver to show the I-beam cursor while it tracks the mouse.

InstanceMethods.Name: draggingImageComponentsWithFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Generates dragging image components with the specified frame in the view.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawFocusRingMaskWithFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the focus ring for the control.

InstanceMethods.Name: focusRingMaskBoundsForFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the bounds of the focus ring mask.

InstanceMethods.Name: calcDrawInfo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Recalculates the cell geometry.

InstanceMethods.Name: cellSizeForBounds:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the minimum size needed to display the receiver, constraining it to the specified rectangle.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawingRectForBounds:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the rectangle within which the receiver draws itself

InstanceMethods.Name: imageRectForBounds:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the rectangle in which the receiver draws its image.

InstanceMethods.Name: titleRectForBounds:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the rectangle in which the receiver draws its title text.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawWithFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the receiver’s border and then draws the interior of the cell.

InstanceMethods.Name: highlightColorWithFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the color the receiver uses when drawing the selection highlight.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawInteriorWithFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Draws the interior portion of the receiver, which includes the image or text portion but does not include the border.

InstanceMethods.Name: highlight:withFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Redraws the receiver with the specified highlight setting.

InstanceMethods.Name: editWithFrame:inView:editor:delegate:event:
InstanceMethods.Description: Begins editing of the receiver’s text using the specified field editor.

InstanceMethods.Name: selectWithFrame:inView:editor:delegate:start:length:
InstanceMethods.Description: Selects the specified text range in the cell's field editor.

InstanceMethods.Name: endEditing:
InstanceMethods.Description: Ends the editing of text in the receiver using the specified field editor.

InstanceMethods.Name: fieldEditorForView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a custom field editor for editing in the view.

InstanceMethods.Name: expansionFrameWithFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the expansion cell frame for the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: drawWithExpansionFrame:inView:
InstanceMethods.Description: Instructs the receiver to draw in an expansion frame.

InstanceMethods.Name: setEntryType:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets how numeric data is formatted in the receiver and places restrictions on acceptable input.

InstanceMethods.Name: entryType
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the type of data the user can type into the receiver.

InstanceMethods.Name: isEntryAcceptable:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns whether a string representing a numeric or date value is formatted in a suitable way for the cell's entry type.

InstanceMethods.Name: setFloatingPointFormat:left:right:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the auto-ranging and floating point number format of the receiver’s cell.

InstanceMethods.Name: setTitleWithMnemonic:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the title of the receiver with one character in the string denoted as an access key.

InstanceMethods.Name: mnemonic
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the character in the receiver’s title that appears underlined for use as a mnemonic.

InstanceMethods.Name: setMnemonicLocation:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sets the character of the receiver’s title to be used as a mnemonic character.

InstanceMethods.Name: mnemonicLocation
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the position of the underlined mnemonic character in the receiver’s title.

InstanceProperties.Name: objectValue
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s value as an Objective-C object.

InstanceProperties.Name: hasValidObjectValue
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value that indicates whether the cell has a valid object value.

InstanceProperties.Name: intValue
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s value as an integer.

InstanceProperties.Name: integerValue
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s value as an NSInteger type.

InstanceProperties.Name: stringValue
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s value as a string.

InstanceProperties.Name: doubleValue
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s value as a double-precision floating-point number.

InstanceProperties.Name: floatValue
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s value as a single-precision floating-point number.

InstanceProperties.Name: type
InstanceProperties.Description: The type of the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: enabled
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell is currently enabled.

InstanceProperties.Name: allowsUndo
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell assumes responsibility for undo operations.

InstanceProperties.Name: bezeled
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell has a bezeled border.

InstanceProperties.Name: bordered
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell draws itself outlined with a plain border.

InstanceProperties.Name: opaque
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell is completely opaque.

InstanceProperties.Name: controlTint
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s control tint.

InstanceProperties.Name: backgroundStyle
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s background style.

InstanceProperties.Name: interiorBackgroundStyle
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s interior background style.

InstanceProperties.Name: allowsMixedState
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell supports three states instead of two.

InstanceProperties.Name: nextState
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s next state.

InstanceProperties.Name: state
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s current state.

InstanceProperties.Name: editable
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell is editable.

InstanceProperties.Name: selectable
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell’s text can be selected.

InstanceProperties.Name: scrollable
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether excess text scrolls past the cell’s bounds.

InstanceProperties.Name: alignment
InstanceProperties.Description: The alignment of the cell’s text.

InstanceProperties.Name: font
InstanceProperties.Description: The font that the cell uses to display text.

InstanceProperties.Name: lineBreakMode
InstanceProperties.Description: The line break mode to use when drawing text in the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: truncatesLastVisibleLine
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell truncates text that does not fit within the cell’s bounds.

InstanceProperties.Name: wraps
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell wraps text whose length that exceeds the cell’s frame.

InstanceProperties.Name: baseWritingDirection
InstanceProperties.Description: The initial writing direction used to determine the actual writing direction for text.

InstanceProperties.Name: attributedStringValue
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s value as an attributed string.

InstanceProperties.Name: allowsEditingTextAttributes
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell allows the editing of its content’s text attributes by the user.

InstanceProperties.Name: importsGraphics
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell supports the importation of images into its text.

InstanceProperties.Name: title
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s title text.

InstanceProperties.Name: action
InstanceProperties.Description: The action performed by the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: target
InstanceProperties.Description: The object that receives the cell’s action messages.

InstanceProperties.Name: continuous
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell sends its action message continuously during mouse tracking.

InstanceProperties.Name: image
InstanceProperties.Description: The image displayed by the cell, if any.

InstanceProperties.Name: tag
InstanceProperties.Description: A tag for identifying the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: formatter
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s formatter object.

InstanceProperties.Name: menu
InstanceProperties.Description: The cell’s contextual menu.

InstanceProperties.Name: acceptsFirstResponder
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell accepts first responder status.

InstanceProperties.Name: showsFirstResponder
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell provides a visual indication that it is the first responder.

InstanceProperties.Name: refusesFirstResponder
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell refuses the first responder status.

InstanceProperties.Name: representedObject
InstanceProperties.Description: The object represented by the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: mouseDownFlags
InstanceProperties.Description: The modifier flags for the last (left) mouse-down event.

InstanceProperties.Name: keyEquivalent
InstanceProperties.Description: The key equivalent associated with clicking the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: focusRingType
InstanceProperties.Description: The type of focus ring to use with the associated view.

InstanceProperties.Name: cellSize
InstanceProperties.Description: The minimum size needed to display the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: controlSize
InstanceProperties.Description: The size of the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: controlView
InstanceProperties.Description: The view associated with the cell.

InstanceProperties.Name: highlighted
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell has a highlighted appearance.

InstanceProperties.Name: sendsActionOnEndEditing
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell’s control object sends its action message when the user finishes editing the cell’s text.

InstanceProperties.Name: wantsNotificationForMarkedText
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell’s field editor should post text change notifications.

InstanceProperties.Name: usesSingleLineMode
InstanceProperties.Description: A Boolean value indicating whether the cell restricts layout and rendering of text to a single line.

InstanceProperties.Name: userInterfaceLayoutDirection
InstanceProperties.Description: The layout direction of the user interface.

TypeProperties.Name: defaultMenu
TypeProperties.Description: Returns the default menu for instances of the cell.

TypeProperties.Name: prefersTrackingUntilMouseUp
TypeProperties.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether tracking stops when the cursor leaves the cell.

TypeProperties.Name: defaultFocusRingType
TypeProperties.Description: Returns the default type of focus ring for the receiver.
